      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "By Binomial Theorem with x=y=1: (1+1)^n = \u03a3 C(n,k) = 2^n.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-4",
      "question": "In Pascal's Triangle, each entry is the sum of:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Two entries directly above it"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "All entries in the previous row"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "The entry above-left and above-right"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Entries in the row below"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "C",
      "explanation": "Pascal's Identity: C(n,k) = C(n-1,k-1) + C(n-1,k), meaning each entry is sum of the two entries above it diagonally.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
